item.title: First sig
item.dc:creator: @ThAt0n36Uy Elijah
item.description:
@ThAt0n36Uy wrote:

Why don’t we get back to the initial argument, or Critiquing the topic posters sig for that matter. I have to agree with Javis that he didn’t do much, but I do feel that he made an image, and deserves credit for what he did do. I don’t think that the issue is really that he did any work or not, but what the result is.

The signature isn’t very good at all. The render, being the focal point of the piece is quite blurry. The C4D in the background is a trend among beginners, and is just a filler in the signature. The text is just default settings for layer styles, but is an attempt at blending the text. It’s quite large, and distracts from the focal point, the render. It’s just the usual beginner signature, and lacks any room for improvement. I think your best course of action is to download some brushes, and find some tutorials. I suggest a grunge tutorial, a render blending tutorial, and a text effect tutorial.

I give it a 1/10.
